AgriBank, Datang, Huadian, KWG, SJM: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-03-11T00:57:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/datang-huadian-galaxy-entertainment-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in  Hong Kong  trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  fell 0.8 percent to 23,614.89. The Hang
Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, declined 0.7 percent to 12,992.50.  Power producers: China’s top five power producers had a
combined loss of 13.7 billion yuan ($2.1 billion) from thermal-
power generation last year, China Electric Power News reported,
citing Zhai Ruoyu, former president of China Datang Corp., the
nation’s second-largest power company.  Huadian Power International Corp. (1071 HK) dropped 0.6
percent to HK$1.55. Datang International Power Generation Co.
(991 HK), China’s biggest publicly traded electricity producer,
increased 1.5 percent to HK$2.70.    Agricultural Bank of China Ltd. (1288)  (1288 HK): The nation’s
fourth-largest bank by market value said its board approved a
plan to sell up to 10 billion yuan ($1.5 billion) of yuan-
denominated bonds in Hong Kong with maturity of no more than
five years. The proceeds will be used to fund demand for loans
and supplement working capital. The stock rose 0.2 percent to
HK$4.15.    Galaxy Entertainment Group Ltd. (27)  (27 HK): The casino
operator part-owned by Permira Advisers LLP expects to increase
its revenue by 20 percent this year, Deputy Chairman Francis Lui
said. The stock gained 0.4 percent to HK$11.32.    Hutchison Whampoa Ltd. (13)  (13 HK): Hutchison Port Holdings
Trust, which manages Chinese port assets for Hutchison Whampoa,
reduced the maximum amount it may raise in an initial public
offering to $5.56 billion, two people with knowledge of the
matter said. The company is offering about 5.4 billion units in
a trust at 99 U.S. cents to $1.03 each in  Singapore , said the
people, who declined to be identified before an announcement.
The units were initially offered at 91 cents to $1.08 each,
according to a sale document sent to investors on Feb. 28.
Hutchison Whampoa gained 0.8 percent to $HK92.75.    KWG Property Holding Ltd. (1813)  (1813 HK): The developer said its
full-year net income rose to 1.28 billion yuan from 720.1
million yuan a year earlier. The stock slid 1.5 percent to
HK$5.32.    SJM Holdings Ltd. (880)  (880 HK): Billionaire  Stanley Ho ’s
dispute with some family members over ownership of their
gambling business has been fully resolved and he has withdrawn
his lawsuit, according to an e-mailed statement from his office.
SJM, controlled by Ho, declined 0.2 percent to HK$12.10.    Value Partners Group Ltd. (806)  (806 HK): The money manager,
backed by China’s second-largest insurance company and U.S.-
based Affiliated Managers Group Inc., said full-year profit for
2010 doubled to HK$653.2 million ($83.9 million) from a year
earlier. The stock fell 1.9 percent to HK$7.96.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Tokyo at 
 knishizawa5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 